description:
Have you ever wondered, “Does God have a plan for my life?” or “What is God’s plan for my life?” Want to learn how to know God’s plan for your life? Pastor Pavel Goia draws lessons from the experiences of Israel’s exodus from Egypt to show God’s purpose for us.
Israel was called to be a kingdom of priests, that is, ministers for Him to the world. In the same way, part of God’s purpose is for us to serve Him by ministering to others. In Hebrews 3, Paul warned spiritual Israel not to follow literal Israel’s example of unbelief and refusal to serve. The warning is for us.  
God has given each of us gifts to be employed in His service and we are accountable to Him for those gifts. In every parable He told, Jesus showed that those who don’t use the gifts lose them and are cut off. Listen as Pastor Goia shares the amazing story of how two mentally handicapped young men were used in a powerful way by God to bring people to Him. If Jesus could use two demoniacs, a donkey, and the woman at the well, what excuse can any of us give for refusing to serve Him?
Do you want to understand Israel’s mistakes and avoid making the same mistakes in your own life? Pastor Goia teaches practical lessons from the experiences of Israel and illustrates them with real life examples from his personal experiences. Discover what you must do to learn God’s plan for your life and fulfill God’s purpose for you.
